	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> Nov. 1852</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">By this days mail I have<lb/> forwarded you a charity sermon delivered by the<lb/> <persName>Revd. Solomon Jacobs</persName> in behalf of the sick and<lb/> indigent.  &#36;300 were collected on that occasion.<lb/>  I beg as a favor that you will notice the<lb/> sermon in the <date>Novr</date> No of the Occident.<lb/>  So far our congregation are very much pleased<lb/> with him particularly his discourses&#44; which<lb/> are forcible&#44; persuasive and eloquent.&#95;&#95;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">He delivered one on last <date>sabbath</date> on &#8220;Free<lb/> Agency&#8222;&#8212;which I deemed his best&#44; &#61; It was<lb/> philosophical &#38; original&#44; logical yet simple<lb/> enough for the most limited mind to comprehend.&#8212;<lb/>  The Reformers are much pleased with him as<lb/> many of them are regular attendants each <date>sabbath</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We hope to effect a reunion.&#61;  The only<lb/> barrier is <persName>Poznanski </persName> &#44; <persName>Jacobs</persName> &#38; a few others&#8212;<lb/>but circumstances will compel them to yield<lb/> in time.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Excuse haste I am very busy</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Nathl Se<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mrs L.</persName> and all your friends</p>
				<p>d<add>&#63;</add> their kindest regards.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We have had a severe &#38; sickly season&#44; and many</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">deaths worry our people&#8212;</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Pen</placeName></p>
		</body>
